      "highlight_excellence": "The Harris-Benedict equation, in both its original and revised forms, is a well-established tool for estimating BMR. It directly incorporates anthropometric data (weight, height) and demographic factors (age, gender) to account for variations in metabolic rate. Recognizing that % Lean Body Mass is NOT a direct input into the standard Harris-Benedict equation demonstrates a precise recall of its components.",
