    "guideline": "Current NCCN and AAD guidelines for Bowen’s disease advise complete surgical excision with 4‑6 mm margins for lesions ≤2 cm when anatomically possible. When excision is not feasible, topical chemotherapeutic agents (5‑FU, imiquimod), cryotherapy, or photodynamic therapy are acceptable alternatives. Sentinel lymph node biopsy is not indicated for intraepithelial SCC.",
