      "address_gaps": "Option D is incorrect. Broders’ grading is an *outdated* system and has *poor* correlation with survival. It’s primarily used for tumor staging and doesn’t reliably predict prognosis. Newer, more sophisticated grading systems (e.g., Masaoka staging) are far more accurate. The question highlights a critical shift in understanding gastric cancer classification and prognostic factors.",
