      "address_gaps": "The question’s weakness lies in its simplicity. While the core concept is sound, it doesn’t probe deeper into the pathophysiology or alternative radiographic presentations. A stronger question might include options related to air-fluid levels, bowel wall thickening, or the differential diagnosis of SBO (e.g., ileus). The answer key’s focus solely on valvulae conniventes is somewhat limiting; recognizing the broader picture of gas distribution is important.",
