    "takeaway": "PLAN: I recommend a focused review of endoscopic findings in duodenal ulcer bleeding, emphasizing the identification and targeted hemostasis of visible vessels. Case studies illustrating the different endoscopic appearances and their associated rebleed rates would be beneficial. Further, a discussion of the pathophysiology of duodenal ulcer bleeding – including the role of gastric acid, mucosal defense mechanisms, and vascular factors – is warranted.",
