      "address_gaps": "Many students struggle with the precise branching patterns of the hepatic arteries. A key gap is often a lack of understanding of the relationship between the SMA, gastroduodenal artery, and the hepatic arterial supply. Furthermore, some may conflate hepatic artery ligation with general liver ischemia, failing to appreciate the specific enzyme changes associated with arterial disruption.",
